			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The reason we see these crashes in Chromium but not in the standalone NaCl build is that Chromium uses tcmalloc, and tcmalloc does some floating point arithmetic:  When I debugged the crash, I found that it happened in Sampler::PickNextSamplingPoint() in third_party/tcmalloc/{chromium,vendor}/src/sampler.cc.

The precision exception occurs when a result can't be represented exactly and the operation drops bits.  For example, the division 1/2 can be represented exactly, but 1/3 cannot.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-12-22T10:29:52.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-12-22T10:29:52.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 2 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3227#c2" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3227/comments/full/2" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>